{"text": "The clove hitch is tied by first passing the running end of the rope around the spar and back over itself to form an X. The running end then passes around the spar again, under the intersection of the last two turns, and both ends are pulled tight. There are several methods of tying it using both hands or one hand.", "embedding": [0.009168059, 0.028343169, -0.19035707, -0.07242981, 0.034610417, -0.010963044, -0.004580211, 0.0056346045, -0.00024898833, -0.042120222, -0.07845606, 0.027327519, 0.060347956, -0.015279151, 0.07124551, -0.012315145, 0.050526302, -0.08614886, 0.045191444, -0.0066396436, -0.048551288, -0.0024186438, -0.0028524683, -0.03409708, 0.014220661, 0.009728857, -0.0033390818, 0.03764302, -0.029308617, -0.000777867, 0.018111685, -0.020414839, -0.00740195, -0.05821941, -0.05620461, -0.05660704, 0.014406974, -0.008552496, -0.006479898, -0.0006416654, 0.05597218, -0.0038196612, 0.038473457, -0.012107218, 0.040214725, -0.060191706, 0.064384945, 0.015317802, 0.06913991, 0.019691411, 0.0036858746, -0.0039898725, -0.053380698, -0.077155456, 0.01993772, 0.008537286, 0.06493833, 0.05979913, 0.058916338, -0.0303946, 0.009507643, 0.041778136, -0.013516243, 0.054725092, 0.069708094, -0.04319035, -0.038783543, 0.051334873, 0.04273703, 0.0127206175, 0.022562686, -0.029672325, 0.07356007, -0.046407767, -0.07289053, 0.023498442, -0.016490592, -0.0052770535, -0.04196679, 0.025404254, 0.026243426, -0.01040732, 0.02602275, 0.022246694, -0.009201568, -0.017723886, -0.047732558, -0.047578752, -0.023819996, 0.035528768, 0.012496293, 0.04842485, 0.057005018, 0.044705596, -0.04374905, 0.011203118, -0.002844868, 0.01758312, -0.043025766, -0.017675009, -0.079153575, 0.010058157, 0.018910319, -0.019817436, 0.0015654524, 0.025772726, 0.022574296, 0.023115316, -0.015235377, -0.016296342, -0.07617864, 0.022762286, -0.031991523, 0.006201481, 0.044143394, 0.048118774, 0.042470846, -0.03372739, 0.023219682, 0.02233774, -0.003943789, -0.008899945, -0.047117166, 0.095611036, 